I ordered an entire pepperoni pizza and garlic bread with a side of Alfredo for delivery via UberEats. 1. The pizza was so dry it was if it had been sitting out, under the warmer, for 4-5 hours on a hot day yet was barely like warm, and the sauce was barely in the middle 2/3 of the pizza. However, the top of the cheese still managed to be a lake of grease, go figure. 2. The garlic bread was a joke. Dripping in grease with huge chunks of garlic as the only "flavor." The marinara was actually cold, and the Alfredo had the consistency and taste of whole milk. The order arrived within 15 minutes of being picked up from the restaurant; these issues definitely cannot be blamed on the driver. $25+ and a complete waste on money, will be giving all the food to an unfortunate homeless person on Claiborne tomorrow morning.

We ordered pizza after leaving Bourbon St (we weren’t the drunk partiers, so alcohol did not affect our review ;) When we got back to our hotel late, we were hungry and had limited options. We ordered pepperoni pizza through GrubHub and were quoted almost an hour on a Friday night, which is not unreasonable.  Less than 45 minutes later, I got a call that the delivery boy was outside the hotel. They had bundled our pizza with another order so we got it early!  The pizza was so good! Not greasy, not too thick or thin, perfect! We ate the whole thing! It was so good that we even ordered it the next evening and got cheese bread and the Bourbon Special Pizza.
